[DhtmlXQ_comment0]sg 20120229 2010 jjls Liu Dahua W Hao Jichao||C93 58 Cannons with 3rd Pawn Advancement vs Screen Horse Defense with 3rd Pawn Advancement||ECCO:C93 ???????????||"Old" GM Liu Dahua, born in 1950, has been a force to reckon with for the past 40+ years. He was the man who stopped GM Hu Ronghua's 10 time winning streak. GM Liu was also consecutive National Champion in 1980,1981. Also known as the Oriental Computer, he set the record for 1 vs 19 in a blindfold Xq match in 1995. This record was only recently broken by GM Jiang Chuan (see bio and facts). GM Liu is still very active in the Xiangqi world in China and has maintained decent rankings consitently. He still wins a lot of tournaments. ||Master Hao Jichao, is another Xq star on the rise. Born in 1985 and a native of Harbin City, he has slowly worked his way up the ladder, making Master by coming in at 17th place in the 2009 Chinese National Singles Competition.||I have chosen this game because it was one of the most exciting games that I have seen in the past month. Master Hao mounts a very fierce attack and even nearly wins, before making a fatal mistage. And GM Liu seized the opportunity to win. Very very exciting. ||For those new to ECCO, ECCO does not take into consideration the which side the first move is made, so although GM Liu plays C8=5, it is still recognized by ECCO as C2=5.[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
